Now, let's calculate the present value of an annuity (savings):

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{PV of an Annuity}&=\text{C}\times\dfrac{1-\left[\dfrac{1}{\left(1+\text{r}\right)^\text{t}}\right]}{\text{r}}\\[15pt]
&=47,000\times\dfrac{1-\left[\dfrac{1}{\left(1+0.071\right)^7}\right]}{0.071}\\[15pt]
&=47,000\times\dfrac{1-\left[\dfrac{1}{1.616316088}\right]}{0.071}\\[15pt]
&=47,000\times\dfrac{1-0.618690866
}{0.071}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\bf\$252,415.91}
\end{aligned}$$

**As it can be seen, the present value of savings is $252,415.91.**
